zards to re-kill for another shot at a charm.  Got a few extra that way, even if it was a little slower.<P>Kistandalius in Ars Magicana sells charms, as does Corinna in Verdistis and sometimes Mpenzak.  This would probably be the fastest and most efficient way to get charms, given the abundance of stuff to trade.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windami</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">any gold and silver ones drop better in any certain area? I only have one gold and 4 silver charms and loads of blue red and green<P><p>[This message has been edited by Windami (edited 22-12-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kiya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windami, go for gold in the Wastelands, after you've become Divine. Sources are Kroxy and the Shaman or the imp chieftains losing them. I saved my empty slots for this area, knowing, which items/armour/weapon I'd keep for the endgame.<BR>Kiya</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Raze</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Clearing out the Dark Forest I got 5 gold charms.  Just before hitting the gong, I have 36 silver charms (a good chunk of those bought).</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windami</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i saved the lizard for the councle of 7 and got an amazing amout of EXP i went from level 37 to level 182 and have a crap load of points spent a point in every skill possible and there is no charm weapon skill that i see there is a charm skill but thats to charm an NPC as your pet it dose nothing i can see for your gear so how once again are you to charm them lmao<P>Wind</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jove</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's the Enchant Item skill <BR>in the Way of the Warrior---&gt;path of the warrior Gods</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windami</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ok i have that skill but is there a place to do this i have tryed droping charms on them i have tryed putting them on the ground to try where and how can this be done can you please tell me the proses of doing this skill it is a pasive skill so i can't select it <P>Wind<P>Please help</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Raze</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you have an item equipped with a Charm Quality of at least one, left click on the item.  A charm pane will open with a number of sockets corresponding to the Charm Quality.  Up to the skill level of Enchant Weapon will be open; the rest, if any, will be closed.  Then just drag and drop charms into open sockets to permanently attach them to the  item.<P>If you have the Enchant Weapon skill and are clicking on a charmable item, but do not see a charm window come up, then charm windows are opening off-screen.  See this <A HREF="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum16/HTML/001493.html" TARGET=_blank>Bug Fix</A> topic.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windami</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">WOOT<P>Finaly got it thanks<P><BR>Wind</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
